definitions.definition: ( weaponry ) A stabbing weapon , similar to a sword but with a short, double-edged blade .
( American football , basketball ) A point scored near the end of the game ( clutch time) to take or increase the scorer's team lead, so that they are likely to win.
examples: His last-minute 3-point dagger silenced the criticism for his so-called failure to come up big in big moments.
